citeinfo.title: Colleges and Universities

descript.abstract: Colleges and Universities: The colleges and university dataset is composed of all Post Secondary Education facilities as defined by the Integrated Post Secondary Education System (IPEDS), National Center for Education Statistics, US Department of Education. Included are Doctoral/Research Universities, Masters Colleges and Universities, Baccalaureate Colleges, Associates Colleges, Theological seminaries, Medical Schools and other health care professions, Schools of engineering and technology, business and management, art, music, design, Law schools, Teachers colleges, Tribal colleges, and other specialized institutions. Overall, this data layer covers all 50 states, as well as Puerto Rico and other assorted U.S. territories.

attracc.attraccr: Attributes fields were populated using the National Center for Educational Statistic's Integrated Postsecondary Education Data System.

qattracc.attracce: The Integrated Postsecondary Education Data System is mandated to gather statistics pertaining to postsecondary educational facilities to analyze trends and provide the public with shcooling options. Facilities that provide data participate in the federal student financial aid programs and are required to file accurate statistics reports in all of the areas provided in this dataset.

dataqual.logic: The Integrated Postsecondary Education Data System uses the physical address provided by the postsecondary institution to geocode the location of the school. Oak Ridge National Laboratory further locates each schoolpoint for the US and Puerto Rico provided through the IPEDS program on the school building. The colleges/universities for the territories may not be found on an entity at this time; they are a work in progress. Shelter_ID is a work in progress at the time of this deliverable. ORNL specifically updates the following fields: LAT, LON, SHELTER_ID, NAICS, and LAST_UPDATE. All other fields are as reported by the Integrated Postsecondary Education Data System by the National Center for Education Statistics.
dataqual.complete: THIS DATASET REPRESENTS A FINAL DELIVERY OF UNIVERSITIES/COLLEGES FOR HSIP 2011.

srcinfo.srccontr: Data provided by the National Center for Education Statistics through the Integrated Postsecondary Education Data System (IPEDS). All postsecondary institutions that receive federal grants are required to provide accurate and complete statistics.
